    "ocr_text": "LF

Mr. John Hurley, Organizer,
Box 248
Chattanooga, Tenn.

Dear Sir and Brother:

Your favor of the 4th instant is received and contents noted. In reply thereto I beg to say that I feel confident Secretary Collins could not have received your letter in regard to the Electrical Workers, or he would have let you had a reply before this. I would suggest that you write him again, addressing him at Pierick Building, Springfield, Ill. In the meantime, I am writing to him.

I note the different pamphlets which you have checked off on the list of literature published by this office, and I am sending you a package under separate cover which from your letter I am confident you can use to good advantage.

With kind regards and hoping to hear from you often, I am,

Fraternally yours,

President
American Federation of Labor.",
    "summary": "A response letter acknowledging receipt of earlier communication, advising to resend a letter to Secretary Collins regarding the Electrical Workers, and confirming the sending of requested pamphlets.",
    "date": "1920-04-06",
    "is_printed": true,
    "is_legible": true
}
